{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἀρά</b>, <br /> <i>Ionic dialect</i> ἀρή, ἡ, <b>prayer,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 15.378, 598, 23.199, 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Opera et Dies” 726, 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “I.” 6(5).43\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἀρὴν ἐποιήσαντο παῖδα γενέσθαι Ἀρίστωνι offered <b>prayers</b> that a child should be born, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 6.63. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>vow,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Inscription Cyprian dialect 83, 147H. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <b>curse, imprecation,</b> ἐξ ἀρέων μητρὸς.. ἥ ῥα θεοῖσι πόλλ᾽ ἀχέουσ᾽ ἠρᾶτο[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 9.566\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; frequently in Trag., mostly in <i>plural</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 910, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 295\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἀρὰς ἀρᾶσθαι,προστιθέναι, ἐξανιέναι, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Phoenissae” 67, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 952, 154(Lyric poetry), 1375; ἐπεύχεσθαι 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Critias” 119e; θέσθαι ἐπί τινας 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Camillus” 13\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: also in <i>singular</i>, πατρὸς δ᾽ ἀ. κρανθήσεται[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 910, compare “Ag.” 457 (Lyric poetry), etc.; ἡ τοῦ νόμου ἀ. 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 871b; ἀρᾷ.. ἔνοχος ἔστω [prev. work] 742b\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>], etc.: in <i>plural</i>, <b>imprecations,</b> frequently in Inscrr. on those who shall mutilate or remove them, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Inscription Magn.” 105.53 (2nd c.BC), “IG” 3.1417ff \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> Ἀρά personified as the goddess of destruction and revenge, ὦ πότνι᾽ Ἀρὰ σεμναί τε θεῶν παῖδες Ἐρινύες[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “El.” III; δεινόπους Ἀρά [prev. author] “OT” 418; but in 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Eumenides” 417 the Erinyes say that Ἀραί\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] is their own name γῆς ὑπα; Ἀρά τ᾽ Ἐρινὺς πατρὸς ἡ μεγασθενής[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Th.” 70; Ἀρᾶς ἱερόν 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Fragmenta” 575. (Hence the Verb ἀράομαι.)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] [<i>Epic dialect</i> always ᾱρ, <i>Attic dialect</i> always ᾰρ.] (From ἀρϝᾱ, compare κάταρ ϝος.)","strongNumber":"G0685","accentedUnicode":"ἀρά","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0142","matchingForm":"αἴρω","stepTransliteration":"airō","gloss":"to take up","_zh_tw_Gloss":"舉起, 提起","_es_Gloss":"levantar","_zh_Gloss":"举起, 提起"},{"strongNumber":"G2671","matchingForm":"κατάρα","stepTransliteration":"katara","gloss":"curse","_zh_tw_Gloss":"咒詛","_es_Gloss":"maldición","_zh_Gloss":"咒诅"}],"shortDef":"curse","mediumDef":"<i>primarily</i> <b>a prayer;</b> more commonly <b>a prayer for evil; curse, cursing, imprecation,</b> <ref='Rom.3.14'>Rom. 3:14</ref>*","stepGloss":"curse","stepTransliteration":"ara","count":1,"_es_Definition":"una oración generalmente malvada","_zh_tw_Definition":"詛咒 (羅 3:14)","_zh_Definition":"诅咒 (罗 3:14)","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"sự rủa; lời nguyền rủa","_zh_tw_Gloss":"咒罵","_es_Gloss":"maldición","_zh_Gloss":"咒骂"}]}